&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for an Insights Manager to join our established qualitative market research team. We are a small, qualitatively focused team providing HCP and patient insights for all types of pharmaceutical business from biotechs to global pharmaceutical brands.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our work focuses on research around product launches and branding, spanning more traditional HCP-focused market research projects through to partnerships with our broader agencies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work closely with our healthcare clients to help their teams turn data into insights and understand its impact on their business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have experience building client relationships, working in a collaborative environment with interest in primary qualitative healthcare market research, data analytics and insight generation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alongside helping to grow the research and insight capability across the group, a key component of this role is managing the administration and delivery of audience metrics practice for Congress stands, using our Congress Measurement Metrics tool and approach, which will involve some travel to European Congresses and liaison with clients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a hybrid role (2 days in the office).&lt;/p&gt;
