&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity to join our world-class live event production team within &lt;strong&gt;Emota&lt;/strong&gt;, a leading brand of over 500 thinkers, creators and makers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a &lt;strong&gt;Production Manager&lt;/strong&gt;, you&#39;ll lead the technical delivery of high-impact live, virtual and hybrid events, owning production from concept to execution. You&#39;ll shape technical solutions, partner with clients and suppliers, and ensure every experience is delivered seamlessly, safely and to the highest creative and technical standards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to one of our Technical Directors, this is a hybrid working position where you will work from a home office, onsite delivery and have access to one of our collaborative, creative offices in either London or Manchester.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;What you&#39;ll be doing&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With responsibilities across multiple productions at any one time, your role will be varied but will include the following key responsibilities:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead onsite and virtual production delivery, ensuring any client and supplier dealings are exercised with the utmost diligence and always with the our business and client in mind&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support with the creation of production budgets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Consider, research and develop the event specification from a technical perspective, including lighting, sound, AV, IT and construction&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with technical suppliers to ensure quality products/services are delivered and all events are specified correctly, to a high standard whilst also being delivered on time and within budget&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Brief crew, suppliers and update requirements throughout the delivery process, creating necessary crew documents&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the creation and distribution of action plans to aid project management, including but not limited to timelines, build schedules, show running orders, contact sheets, and crew packs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide accurate responses to client requests. Being aware of any changes in requirements and making updates accordingly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creation of the production execution plan. Including all administration necessities and deliver projects in a safe and controlled manner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Actively follow all approval procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure Live Events quality and sustainability procedures are followed on each project and ensure appropriate records are maintained&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage all equipment and event accessories&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide hands-on production management support to virtual/live projects and pitches&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mange technical budgets and flag any anomalies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain up to date technical knowledge and expertise around delivery techniques and equipment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;What you need to have&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
